As William James declared when the monument in the Regimen‚Äôs honor (the first in the nation to honor Black soldiers) was dedicated 125 years ago tomorrow: 

‚ÄúThere they march, warm-blooded champions of a better day for man.‚Äù https://t.co/1rLIzzobUj

Shaw, a young White man born to privilege, volunteered to lead the all-Black Regimen straight into the heart of the Confederacy. The Black men who volunteered for duty knew that the result was likely death, or capture and perpetual enslavement. And yet, they fought; for America.
This Memorial Day, I‚Äôm thinking of the extraordinary courage and timeless lessons of the 54th Massachusetts Infantry Regimen under the command of Robert Gould Shaw. üá∫üá∏‚ù§Ô∏è
